<TITLE> 16 yr old dies 'mysteriously' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Narail, Apr 28 (bdnews24.com)  A sixteen-year-old boy died mysteriously at Lohagara upazila in Narail on Wednesday at around 4am. The dead has been identified as Rakibul Islam, son of Abdul Hai of Kola village. Faruque Hossain, a sub-inspector of Lohagara Police Station told bdnews24.com that Rakibul died in the garden beside his house when he was going to the mosque to say prayers at dawn. The body had no signs of injury. Abdul Hai said that they had no dispute with others. "It is very mysterious." Faruque said that the authorities allowed the body to be buried without post mortem because of a request from Rakibul's family and locals. Md Palash, chairman of Dighalia union told bdnews24.com that it was a mysterious death. "I requested the administration to skip autopsy." bdn
